lass="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.352140095&amp;id=fig10d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.352140095/asset/images/large/rg.352140095.fig11a.jpeg" height="603" width="814" aria-labelledby="fig11a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span> Gallbladder polyp caused by invasive hepatocellular carcinoma in a 49-year-old man with cirrhosis. US <b>(a)</b> and axial contrast-enhanced T1-weighted MR <b>(b)</b> images show a large mass in the right hepatic lobe (arrowheads) that invades through the gallbladder wall and protrudes as an intraluminal polypoid mass (arrow).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.352140095&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.352140095/asset/images/large/rg.352140095.fig11b.jpeg" height="603" width="511" aria-labelledby="fig11b" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11b</span> Gallbladder polyp caused by invasive hepatocellular carcinoma in a 49-year-old man with cirrhosis. US <b>(a)</b> and axial contrast-enhanced T1-weighted MR <b>(b)</b> images show a large mass in the right hepatic lobe (arrowheads) that invades through the gallbladder wall and protrudes as an intraluminal polypoid mass (arrow).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.352140095&amp;id=fig11b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.352140095/asset/images/large/rg.352140095.fig12.jpeg" height="1630" width="2700" aria-labelledby="fig12" lo